  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "There are currently 2 issues with clang-tidy:\r\n1. When clang-tidy has an error, the CI job still reports back \"pass\"\r\n2. clang-tidy *always* has errors on every PR such as the following:\r\n`error: invalid argument '-std=c++14' not allowed with 'C' [clang-diagnostic-error]`\r\n`error: cannot use 'throw' with exceptions disabled [clang-diagnostic-error]`\r\n\r\nI'm still troubleshooting issue 1. [This PR](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/pull/9140) added a fix (`-o pipefail`) to unmask an error in `git clone`, but for some reason errors in clang-tidy itself are still being swallowed.\r\n\r\nFor issue 2 I'm suspecting that it's caused by [this change](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/pull/8628/files#diff-bd94107c801983d39bc0bd34030f0b12L62) in `gen_compilation_database.py` which removes the hard-coded `clang++` compiler invocation in favor of whatever compiler the Bazel magic returns. From observing my `compile_commands.json`, it appears to be the value of `$CC`, not `$CXX` (i.e. I get `gcc` instead of `g++`) which explains why clang-tidy doesn't like exceptions or `-std=c++14`. Interestingly, `-x c++` is correctly set, although I believe to correctly compile C++ with a C compiler you also need to link the stdlib, such as `-lc++`.\r\n\r\ncc @lizan ",
